ector partners and has promoted engagement of CS in parter fora, such as the recently held JANS workshop, in which there was a specific session for CS.'),(5913,285,'21','2005','0.0','2009','0.0','All World Bank disbursements given to the Government of Ethiopia.'),(5914,285,'22','2005','0.0','2009','0.0','Under the PBS project, the WB provides support in the form of block grants to regions to support basic services (source: interview with TTL).'),(5915,285,'23','2005','0.0','2009','0.0',''),(5939,287,'1','2005','No','2009','No','Does not currently have an IHP+ Country Compact or equivalent agreement.'),(5940,287,'2','2005','16580000.0','2009','16840000.0','For a detailed record of disbursements for calendar years 2005 and 2009 please see excel tab 2DPa, which breaks down monthly disbursements for all active projects during these calendar years.'),(5941,287,'3','','16580000.0','','16840000.0','The WB disburses directly to the Government of Burkina Faso.'),(5942,287,'4','2005','497400.0','2009','842000.0','While some TA has been provided through staff support and trust funds (Health Results Innovation Trust Fund - after CY09), overall provision of technical assistance is limited in Burkina Faso.ased on discussions with the TTL and considering variance across projects in relevant fiscal years, we have provided estimates for % of TA disbursed in respective calendar years.'),(5943,287,'5','','497400.0','','842000.0','For more detailed information and justification for this rating based on the IHP+ Results \"Guide to Key Terms and Definitions\"please see tab 2DPb and relevant sources noted therein.'),(5944,287,'6','2005','16580000.0','2009','16840000.0','Please note that totals given for \"health sector aid for the government sector ($USD)\" (2DPa) and \"health sector aid ($USD) did you disburse at country level\"(2DPc) are the same, as the World Bank disburses all funds through partner governments at the country level.'),(5945,287,'7','','16580000.0','','16840000.0','For 